        <abstract>
            <p>Asks JDH why so many plants are protected by a thin layer of waxy matter or with fine hairs.</p> 
<p>Wrote to John Smith for a plant of <hi rend="italic">Oxalis sensitiva</hi>, but it has not acted well.</p> 
            <p>Rejoices over Ayrton’s retirement. Hopes W. P. Adam, his successor, is a good sort of man.</p>
        </abstract>
